<subSubSection pageNumber="331" type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="331">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="331">Note:</emphasis>
Bullock (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="331">Kew Bull.</emphasis>
3: 54. 1948) discussed this name in detail and clearly regarded a sheet at LINN as &quot;the Linnean type&quot;. However, his text does not distinguish between sheets 997.56 and 997.57, which are evidently not part of a single gathering (so Art. 9.15 does not apply). Kroner (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="331">
Mitt. Bot. Staatssamml. 
<normalizedToken originalValue="MÃ¼nchen">Muenchen</normalizedToken>
</emphasis>
16: 111. 1980) explicitly treated sheet 997.56 as the 
<typeStatus>lectotype</typeStatus>
, but it is a Tulbagh collection, sent to Linnaeus only in 1769 and which cannot therefore have been original material for the name.
</paragraph>
